cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.HC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing verbal and non-verbal signals of depression using acoustic and text modalities. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel attention-based deep neural network for depression level estimation. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is relevant as the paper uses visual modalities for depression level estimation. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is relevant as the paper uses acoustic modalities for depression level estimation. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper deals with analyzing human emotions and mental health.
